An Act relating to sexual assault nurse examiners;
amending Section 2, Chapter 343, O.S.L. 2023 (19 O.S.
Supp. 2025, Section 215.41), which relates to sexual
assault nurse examiners; and deleting sunset date.
SUBJECT: Sexual assault nurse examiners
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 343, O.S.L.
2023 (19 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 215.41), is amended to read as
follows:
Section 215.41. Subject to availability of funding, there is
established until October 1, 2025, within the District Attorneys
Council under the direction of the Executive Coordinator of the
District Attorneys Council, the position of Sexual Assault Nurse
Examiner (SANE) Statewide Coordinator. The Statewide Coordinator
shall oversee forensic medical examination training throughout the
state, recruit and develop SANE professionals, create and expand
local Sexual Assault Nurse Examiner programs and Sexual Assault
Response Team programs throughout this state, and coordinate
payments from the Sexual Assault Examination Fund.

Passed the House of Representatives the 11th day of March, 2026.
Presiding Officer of the House
of Representatives
Passed the Senate the 28th day of April, 2026.
